  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<h3>Beginners skiing and snowboarding in Sauze d'Oulx</h3>
<p>Beginners should think about signing up to ski school before tackling the mountain. Sportinia is where you will find the ski school meeting place and the sunny, sheltered nursery slope is ideal for complete beginners.</p>
<p>After just a few day’s tuition, above the beginners area you will find Blue 12 &amp; 13, ideal wide runs to put all that practise into action and ideal for building your confidence. By the end of the week, if you feel ready, there are red routes back into Sauze. Number 30 from the top of the Sportina chair to the bottom of the Clotes chairlift will be a testing challenge for those who want to progress onto tougher terrain. </p>
<h3>Intermediate skiing and snowboarding in Sauze d'Oulx</h3>
<p>Sauze d’Oulx is an exceptional resort for intermediate skiers. There is a fantastic range of cruising terrain ideal for improving your technique and building your confidence. As a result, snowboarding is also a popular past time. We like to head up to the top of the Moncrons where the red pistes are generally less crowded.</p>
<p>Intermediate skiers can cover significant distances and there is varied skiing, both above and below the tree line. You can easily access the three main areas of Clotes, Sportinia and Genevris using the interlinking lifts. It is also simple to ski to Sestriere and the enjoyable runs of Sansicario.</p>
<p>Travelling to Montgenevre, across the Italian/French boarder is a great day trip. The French resort is also a part of the Milky Way area and well worth a visit, best of alkl you get 2 days included in your area lift pass. </p>
<h3>Advanced skiing and snowboarding in Sauze d'Oulx</h3>
<p>Our favourite piste on the mountain is the Olimpico. Take the chairlift to the top of Mount Fraiteve, from here a mixture of red and black piste drops all the way into Sansicario village. This long and challenging run will really put your stamina to the test!</p>
<p>If you fancy a challenging run, number 25 known as Rio Nero is where you want to head. This exciting run starts as a narrow black run and requires excellent control as you navigate the steep piste beneath you. As you descend towards and past the Colo chairlift the run widens, perfect for mastering beautiful wide parallel turns.</p>
<p>Advanced skiers will enjoy neighbouring Sestriere too. The higher resort offers several steep, challenging blacks as well as dedicated mogul fields.</p>
<h3>Off piste and snow parks in Sauze d'Oulx</h3>
<p>The Milky Way area also provides several opportunities to ski off-piste. Free riders can head to the Moncrons, which has possibly the best powder conditions on the mountain. Montgenevre, across the French border, has an excellent reputation for its off-piste with some iconic routes.</p>
<h3>Cross-country skiing in Sauze d'Oulx</h3>
<p>Sauze d'Oulx offers a fantastic range for cross-country ski enthusiasts. The resort has over 25 kilometres of runs for you to use, catering to both sporty skiers and those who like to cruise and take in the stunning mountain scenery.</p>]]></generalInformation>
